{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Now when we think of our senses,"},{"time":5000,"text":"we don't usually think of the reasons"},{"time":7000,"text":"why they probably evolved, from a biological perspective."},{"time":9000,"text":"We don't really think of the evolutionary need"},{"time":12000,"text":"to be protected by our senses,"},{"time":14000,"text":"but that's probably why our senses really evolved --"},{"time":16000,"text":"to keep us safe, to allow us to live."},{"time":19000,"text":"Really when we think of our senses,"},{"time":21000,"text":"or when we think of the loss of the sense,"},{"time":23000,"text":"we really think about something more like this:"},{"time":25000,"text":"the ability to touch something luxurious, to taste something delicious,"},{"time":28000,"text":"to smell something fragrant,"},{"time":30000,"text":"to see something beautiful."},{"time":32000,"text":"This is what we want out of our senses."},{"time":34000,"text":"We want beauty; we don't just want function."},{"time":37000,"text":"And when it comes to sensory restoration,"},{"time":39000,"text":"we're still very far away from being able to provide beauty."},{"time":42000,"text":"And that's what I'd like to talk to you a little bit about today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"Likewise for hearing."},{"time":47000,"text":"When we think about why we hear,"},{"time":49000,"text":"we don't often think about the ability to hear an alarm or a siren,"},{"time":52000,"text":"although clearly that's an important thing."},{"time":54000,"text":"Really what we want to hear is music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"So many of you know that that's Beethoven's Seventh Symphony."},{"time":74000,"text":"Many of you know that he was deaf, or near profoundly deaf,"},{"time":77000,"text":"when he wrote that."},{"time":79000,"text":"Now I'd like to impress upon you"},{"time":81000,"text":"how unusual it is that we can hear music."},{"time":84000,"text":"Music is just one of the strangest things that there is."},{"time":87000,"text":"It's acoustic vibrations in the air,"},{"time":90000,"text":"little waves of energy in the air that tickle our eardrum."},{"time":93000,"text":"Somehow in tickling our eardrum"},{"time":95000,"text":"that transmits energy down our hearing bones,"},{"time":97000,"text":"which get converted to a fluid impulse inside the cochlea"},{"time":100000,"text":"and then somehow converted into an electrical signal in our auditory nerves"},{"time":103000,"text":"that somehow wind up in our brains"},{"time":106000,"text":"as a perception of a song or a beautiful piece of music."},{"time":109000,"text":"That process is entirely abstract and very, very unusual."},{"time":112000,"text":"And we could discuss that topic alone for days"},{"time":115000,"text":"to really try to figure out, how is it that we hear something that's emotional"},{"time":119000,"text":"from something that starts out as a vibration in the air?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"Turns out that if you have hearing loss,"},{"time":124000,"text":"most people that lose their hearing"},{"time":126000,"text":"lose it at what's called the cochlea, the inner ear."},{"time":129000,"text":"And it's at the hair cell level that they do this."},{"time":132000,"text":"Now if you had to pick a sense to lose,"},{"time":134000,"text":"I have to be very honest with you"},{"time":136000,"text":"and say, we're better at restoring hearing"},{"time":138000,"text":"than we are at restoring any sense that there is."},{"time":140000,"text":"In fact, nothing even actually comes close"},{"time":142000,"text":"to our ability to restore hearing."},{"time":144000,"text":"And as a physician and a surgeon, I can confidently tell my patients"},{"time":147000,"text":"that if you had to pick a sense to lose,"},{"time":149000,"text":"we are the furthest along medically and surgically with hearing."},{"time":153000,"text":"As a musician, I can tell you"},{"time":155000,"text":"that if I had to have a cochlear implant,"},{"time":157000,"text":"I'd be heartbroken. I'd just be plainly heartbroken,"},{"time":159000,"text":"because I know that music would never sound the same to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"Now this is a video that I'm going to show you"},{"time":166000,"text":"of a girl who's born deaf."},{"time":168000,"text":"She's in a very supportive environment."},{"time":170000,"text":"Her mother's doing everything she can."},{"time":172000,"text":"Okay, play that video please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"(Video) Mother: That's an owl."},{"time":176000,"text":"Owl, yeah."},{"time":183000,"text":"Owl. Owl."},{"time":186000,"text":"Yeah."},{"time":193000,"text":"Baby. Baby."},{"time":196000,"text":"You want it?"},{"time":199000,"text":"(Kiss)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"Charles Limb: Now despite everything going for this child"},{"time":204000,"text":"in terms of family support"},{"time":206000,"text":"and simple infused learning,"},{"time":208000,"text":"there is a limitation to what a child who's deaf, an infant who was born deaf,"},{"time":211000,"text":"has in this world"},{"time":213000,"text":"in terms of social, educational, vocational opportunities."},{"time":216000,"text":"I'm not saying that they can't live a beautiful, wonderful life."},{"time":219000,"text":"I'm saying that they're going to face obstacles"},{"time":221000,"text":"that most people who have normal hearing will not have to face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"Now hearing loss and the treatment for hearing loss"},{"time":226000,"text":"has really evolved in the past 200 years."},{"time":228000,"text":"I mean literally,"},{"time":230000,"text":"they used to do things like stick ear-shaped objects onto your ears"},{"time":233000,"text":"and stick funnels in."},{"time":235000,"text":"And that was the best you could do for hearing loss."},{"time":237000,"text":"Back then you couldn't even look at the eardrum."},{"time":239000,"text":"So it's not too surprising"},{"time":241000,"text":"that there were no good treatments for hearing loss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"And now today we have the modern multi-channel cochlear implant,"},{"time":245000,"text":"which is an outpatient procedure."},{"time":247000,"text":"It's surgically placed inside the inner ear."},{"time":249000,"text":"It takes about an hour and a half to two hours, depending on where it's done,"},{"time":251000,"text":"under general anesthesia."},{"time":253000,"text":"And in the end, you achieve something like this"},{"time":255000,"text":"where an electrode array is inserted inside the cochlea."},{"time":258000,"text":"Now actually, this is quite crude"},{"time":260000,"text":"in comparison to our regular inner ear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"But here is that same girl who is implanted now."},{"time":265000,"text":"This is her 10 years later."},{"time":267000,"text":"And this is a video that was taken"},{"time":269000,"text":"by my surgical mentor, Dr. John Niparko, who implanted her."},{"time":271000,"text":"If we could play this video please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"(Video) John Niparko: So you've written two books?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"Girl: I have written two books. (Mother: Was the other one a book or a journal entry?)"},{"time":279000,"text":"Girl: No, the other one was a book. (Mother: Oh, okay.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"JN: Well this book has seven chapters,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and the last chapter"},{"time":289000,"text":"is entitled \"The Good Things About Being Deaf.\""},{"time":293000,"text":"Do you remember writing that chapter?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"Girl: Yes I do. I remember writing every chapter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"JN: Yeah."},{"time":301000,"text":"Girl: Well sometimes my sister can be kind of annoying."},{"time":305000,"text":"So it comes in handy to not be annoyed by her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"JN: I see. And who is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"Girl: Holly. (JN: Okay.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"Mother: Her sister. (JN: Her sister.) Girl: My sister."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"JN: And how can you avoid being annoyed by her?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"Girl: I just take off my CI, and I don't hear anything."},{"time":322000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":324000,"text":"It comes in handy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"JN: So you don't want to hear everything that's out there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"Girl: No."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"CL: And so she's phenomenal."},{"time":333000,"text":"And there's no way that you can't look at that as an overwhelming success."},{"time":336000,"text":"It is. It's a huge success story in modern medicine."},{"time":339000,"text":"However, despite this incredible facility"},{"time":342000,"text":"that some cochlear implant users display with language,"},{"time":344000,"text":"you turn on the radio and all of a sudden they can't hear music almost at all."},{"time":348000,"text":"In fact, most implant users really struggle"},{"time":350000,"text":"and dislike music because it sounds so bad."},{"time":353000,"text":"And so when it comes to this idea"},{"time":355000,"text":"of restoring beauty to somebody's life,"},{"time":357000,"text":"we have a long way to go when it comes to audition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359000,"text":"Now there are a lot of reasons for that."},{"time":361000,"text":"I mentioned earlier the fact"},{"time":363000,"text":"that music is a different capacity because it's abstract."},{"time":365000,"text":"Language is very different. Language is very precise."},{"time":367000,"text":"In fact, the whole reason we use it"},{"time":369000,"text":"is because it has semantic-specificity."},{"time":371000,"text":"When you say a word,"},{"time":373000,"text":"what you care is that word was perceived correctly."},{"time":375000,"text":"You don't care that the word sounded pretty"},{"time":377000,"text":"when it was spoken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379000,"text":"Music is entirely different."},{"time":381000,"text":"When you hear music, if it doesn't sound good, what's the point?"},{"time":383000,"text":"There's really very little point in listening to music"},{"time":385000,"text":"when it doesn't sound good to you."},{"time":387000,"text":"The acoustics of music are much harder than those of language."},{"time":390000,"text":"And you can see on this figure,"},{"time":392000,"text":"that the frequency range"},{"time":394000,"text":"and the decibel range, the dynamic range of music"},{"time":396000,"text":"is far more heterogeneous."},{"time":398000,"text":"So if we had to design a perfect cochlear implant,"},{"time":400000,"text":"what we would try to do"},{"time":402000,"text":"is target it to be able to allow music transmission."},{"time":405000,"text":"Because I always view music as the pinnacle of hearing."},{"time":408000,"text":"If you can hear music,"},{"time":410000,"text":"you should be able to hear anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"Now the problems begin first with pitch perception."},{"time":415000,"text":"I mean, most of us know that pitch is a fundamental building block of music."},{"time":418000,"text":"And without the ability to perceive pitch well,"},{"time":420000,"text":"music and melody is a very difficult thing to do --"},{"time":423000,"text":"forget about a harmony and things like that."},{"time":425000,"text":"Now this is a MIDI arrangement of Rachmaninoff's Prelude."},{"time":428000,"text":"Now if we could just play this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"Okay, now if we consider"},{"time":457000,"text":"that in a cochlear implant patient"},{"time":459000,"text":"pitch perception could be off as much as two octaves,"},{"time":462000,"text":"let's see what happens here"},{"time":464000,"text":"when we randomize this to within one semitone."},{"time":466000,"text":"We would be thrilled if we had one semitone pitch perception in cochlear implant users."},{"time":469000,"text":"Go ahead and play this one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"Now my goal in showing you that"},{"time":496000,"text":"is to show you that music is not robust to degradation."},{"time":498000,"text":"You distort it a little bit, especially in terms of pitch, and you've changed it."},{"time":502000,"text":"And it might be that you kind of like that."},{"time":504000,"text":"That's kind of hypnotic."},{"time":506000,"text":"But it certainly wasn't the way the music was intended."},{"time":508000,"text":"And you're not hearing the same thing"},{"time":510000,"text":"that most people who have normal hearing are hearing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"Now the other issue comes with,"},{"time":514000,"text":"not just the ability to tell pitches apart,"},{"time":516000,"text":"but the ability to tell sounds apart."},{"time":518000,"text":"Most cochlear implant users cannot tell the difference between an instrument."},{"time":521000,"text":"If we could play these two sound clips in succession."},{"time":523000,"text":"(Trumpet)"},{"time":525000,"text":"The trumpet."},{"time":527000,"text":"And the second one."},{"time":529000,"text":"(Violin)"},{"time":530000,"text":"That's a violin."},{"time":532000,"text":"These have similar wave forms. They're both sustained instruments."},{"time":534000,"text":"Cochlear implant users cannot tell the difference"},{"time":536000,"text":"between these instruments."},{"time":538000,"text":"The sound quality, or the sound of the sound"},{"time":540000,"text":"is how I like to describe timbre, tone color --"},{"time":542000,"text":"they cannot tell these things whatsoever."},{"time":544000,"text":"This implant is not transmitting"},{"time":547000,"text":"the quality of music that usually provides things like warmth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"Now if you look at the brain of an individual who has a cochlear implant"},{"time":553000,"text":"and you have them listen to speech,"},{"time":555000,"text":"have them listen to rhythm and have them listen to melody,"},{"time":557000,"text":"what you find is that the auditory cortex"},{"time":559000,"text":"is the most active during speech."},{"time":561000,"text":"You would think that because these implants are optimized for speech,"},{"time":563000,"text":"they were designed for speech."},{"time":565000,"text":"But actually if you look at melody,"},{"time":567000,"text":"what you find is that there's very little cortical activity"},{"time":569000,"text":"in implant users compared with normal hearing controls."},{"time":572000,"text":"So for whatever reason,"},{"time":574000,"text":"this implant is not successfully stimulating auditory cortices"},{"time":577000,"text":"during melody perception."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"Now the next question is,"},{"time":582000,"text":"well how does it really sound?"},{"time":584000,"text":"Now we've been doing some studies"},{"time":586000,"text":"to really get a sense of what sound quality is like for these implant users."},{"time":589000,"text":"I'm going to play you two clips of Usher,"},{"time":591000,"text":"one which is normal"},{"time":593000,"text":"and one which has almost no high frequencies, almost no low frequencies"},{"time":595000,"text":"and not even that many mid frequencies."},{"time":597000,"text":"Go ahead and play that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603000,"text":"(Limited Frequency Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"I had patients tell me that those sound the same."},{"time":612000,"text":"They cannot differentiate sound quality differences"},{"time":615000,"text":"between those two clips."},{"time":617000,"text":"Again, we are very, very far away in just getting to where we want to get to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620000,"text":"Now the question comes to mind: Is there any hope?"},{"time":623000,"text":"And yes, there is hope."},{"time":625000,"text":"Now I don't know if anybody knows who this is."},{"time":627000,"text":"This is ... does somebody know?"},{"time":629000,"text":"This is Beethoven."},{"time":632000,"text":"Now why would we know what Beethoven's skull looks like?"},{"time":635000,"text":"Because his grave was exhumed."},{"time":637000,"text":"And it turns out that his temporal bones were harvested when he died"},{"time":640000,"text":"to try to look at the cause of his deafness,"},{"time":642000,"text":"which is why he has molding clay"},{"time":644000,"text":"and his skull is bulging out on the side there."},{"time":646000,"text":"But Beethoven composed music"},{"time":648000,"text":"long after he lost his hearing."},{"time":650000,"text":"What that suggests is that, even in the case of hearing loss,"},{"time":653000,"text":"the capacity for music remains."},{"time":655000,"text":"The brains remain hardwired for music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659000,"text":"I've been very lucky to work with Dr. David Ryugo"},{"time":661000,"text":"where I've been working on deaf cats that are white"},{"time":664000,"text":"and trying to figure out what happens when we give them cochlear implants."},{"time":667000,"text":"This is a cat that's been trained to respond to a trumpet for food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":686000,"text":"Text: Beethoven doesn't excite her."},{"time":689000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":701000,"text":"The \"1812 Overture\" isn't worth waking for."},{"time":706000,"text":"(Trumpet)"},{"time":716000,"text":"But she jumps to action when called to duty!"},{"time":719000,"text":"(Trumpet)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":723000,"text":"CL: Now I'm not suggesting"},{"time":725000,"text":"that the cat is hearing that trumpet the way we're hearing it."},{"time":728000,"text":"I'm suggesting that with training"},{"time":730000,"text":"you can imbue a musical sound with significance,"},{"time":733000,"text":"even in a cat."},{"time":735000,"text":"If we were to direct efforts"},{"time":737000,"text":"towards training cochlear implant users to hear music --"},{"time":740000,"text":"because right now there's virtually no effort put towards that,"},{"time":743000,"text":"no rehabilitative strategies,"},{"time":745000,"text":"very little in the way of technological advances to actually improve music --"},{"time":748000,"text":"we would come a long way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"Now I want to show you one last video."},{"time":753000,"text":"And this is of a student of mine named Joseph"},{"time":755000,"text":"who I had the good fortune to work with for three years in my lab."},{"time":758000,"text":"He's deaf, and he learned to play the piano"},{"time":761000,"text":"after he received the cochlear implant."},{"time":763000,"text":"And here's a video of Joseph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"(Video) Joseph: I was born in 1986."},{"time":813000,"text":"And at about four months old,"},{"time":815000,"text":"I was diagnosed with profoundly severe hearing loss."},{"time":817000,"text":"Not long after,"},{"time":819000,"text":"I was fitted with hearing aids."},{"time":821000,"text":"But although these hearing aids"},{"time":823000,"text":"were the most powerful hearing aids on the market at the time,"},{"time":825000,"text":"they weren't very helpful."},{"time":827000,"text":"So as a result, I had to rely on lip reading a lot,"},{"time":832000,"text":"and I couldn't really hear what people were saying."},{"time":834000,"text":"When I was 12 years old,"},{"time":836000,"text":"I was one of the first few people in Singapore"},{"time":839000,"text":"who underwent cochlear implantation."},{"time":842000,"text":"And not long after I got my cochlear implant,"},{"time":846000,"text":"I started learning how to play piano."},{"time":848000,"text":"And it was absolutely wonderful."},{"time":850000,"text":"Since then, I've never looked back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"CL: Joseph is phenomenal. He's brilliant."},{"time":854000,"text":"He is now a medical student at Yale University,"},{"time":856000,"text":"and he's contemplating a surgical career --"},{"time":858000,"text":"one of the first deaf individuals to consider a career in surgery."},{"time":861000,"text":"There are almost no deaf surgeons anywhere."},{"time":864000,"text":"And this is really unheard of stuff, and this is all because of this technology."},{"time":867000,"text":"And the fact that he can play the piano like that"},{"time":869000,"text":"is a testament to his brain."},{"time":871000,"text":"Truth of the matter is you can play the piano without a cochlear implant,"},{"time":874000,"text":"because all you have to do is press the keys at the right time."},{"time":876000,"text":"You don't actually have to hear it."},{"time":878000,"text":"I know he doesn't hear well, because I've heard him do Karaoke."},{"time":881000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":883000,"text":"And it's one of the most awful things --"},{"time":886000,"text":"heartwarming, but awful."},{"time":888000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":890000,"text":"And so there is certainly a lot of hope,"},{"time":892000,"text":"but there's a lot more that needs to be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"So I just want to conclude with the following words."},{"time":896000,"text":"When it comes to restoration of hearing,"},{"time":898000,"text":"we have certainly come a long way, a remarkably long way."},{"time":901000,"text":"And we have a much longer way to go"},{"time":904000,"text":"when it comes to the idea of restoring perfect hearing."},{"time":906000,"text":"And let me tell you right now,"},{"time":908000,"text":"it's fine that we would all be very happy with speech."},{"time":910000,"text":"But I tell you, if we lost our hearing,"},{"time":912000,"text":"if anyone here suddenly lost your hearing,"},{"time":914000,"text":"you would want perfect hearing back."},{"time":916000,"text":"You wouldn't want decent hearing, you would want perfect hearing."},{"time":919000,"text":"Restoration of basic sensory function is critical."},{"time":922000,"text":"And I don't mean to understate"},{"time":924000,"text":"how important it is to restore basic function."},{"time":926000,"text":"But it's really restoration of the ability to perceive beauty"},{"time":929000,"text":"where we can get inspiring."},{"time":931000,"text":"And I don't think that we should give up on beauty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"And I want to thank you for your time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}